							is attached to the front flyleaf. <name key="ArnMag001" type="person">Árni
								Magnússon</name> wrote on it: <q>Ur bok Pals Widalins Lógman<ex>n</ex>s in octavo.</q>
							A modern hand added in pencil at the bottom of the leaf: <q>Fra bl. 2r</q>.
							<note>This AM-slip belongs to <ref>AM 100 8vo CU1</ref>.</note>
						</p>
						<p>There is a loose slip in the back of the manuscript containing information about the scribe of one of the parts:
